  "title": "Arcs and Sectors",
  "content": "<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Understanding Arcs and Sectors</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Arcs and sectors are parts of circles. An <strong>arc</strong> is a piece of the <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">circle</strong></strong>'s edge (<strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">circumference</strong></strong>), and a <strong>sector</strong> is a \"slice\" of the circleâ€”like a pizza slice! Once you understand how to work with fractions of a circle, these problems become easy.</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Circle Parts Review</h3>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"380\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 380\">\n  <circle cx=\"200\" cy=\"200\" r=\"120\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 200 200 L 320 200 A 120 120 0 0 1 260 304 Z\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 320 200 A 120 120 0 0 1 260 304\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" stroke-width=\"4\"/>\n  <text x=\"280\" y=\"240\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#ef4444\" font-weight=\"bold\">arc</text>\n  <text x=\"240\" y=\"260\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#2563eb\" font-weight=\"bold\">sector</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"360\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Arc = part of circle | Sector = pie slice</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Radius (r):</strong> <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Distance</strong></strong> from center to edge</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Diameter (d):</strong> Distance across through center = 2r</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Circumference (C):</strong> Distance around the circle = 2Ï€r = Ï€d</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Area</strong></strong> (A):</strong> Space inside the circle = Ï€rÂ²</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Arc:</strong> Part of the circumference</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Sector:</strong> \"Pizza slice\" part of the area</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">The Key Idea: Fractions of a Circle</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">A full circle has <strong>360Â°</strong>. If your central angle is Î¸ degrees, then you have <strong>Î¸/360</strong> of the whole circle!</p>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">ðŸ’¡ The Master Formula:</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">Fraction of circle =  Î¸/360</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">If Î¸ = 90Â°, you have 90/360 = 1/4 of the circle</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">If Î¸ = 180Â°, you have 180/360 = 1/2 of the circle</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">If Î¸ = 120Â°, you have 120/360 = 1/3 of the circle</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Arc Length</strong></strong> Formula</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Arc length is a <strong>fraction of the circumference</strong>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #f59e0b; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Arc Length = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</strong>\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>In words:</strong> Take the fraction of the circle, multiply by the full circumference!</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"350\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 350\">\n  <circle cx=\"200\" cy=\"170\" r=\"100\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 200 170 L 300 170 A 100 100 0 0 1 200 270 Z\" fill=\"#fef3c7\" stroke=\"#f59e0b\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"170\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"70\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,3\"/>\n  <text x=\"260\" y=\"240\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#f59e0b\" font-weight=\"bold\">90Â°</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"320\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\">90Â° out of 360Â° = Â¼ of circle</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 1: Arc Length</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> A circle has radius 10. What is the length of a 90Â° arc?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Arc Length = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r<br>\n  Arc Length = (90/360) Ã— 2Ï€(10)<br>\n  Arc Length = (1/4) Ã— 20Ï€<br>\n  Arc Length = 5Ï€\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Sector Area</strong></strong> Formula</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Sector area is a <strong>fraction of the total area</strong>.</p>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #10b981; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</strong>\n</p>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>In words:</strong> Take the fraction of the circle, multiply by the full area!</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"360\" viewBox=\"0 0 400 360\">\n  <circle cx=\"200\" cy=\"180\" r=\"110\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 200 180 L 310 180 A 110 110 0 0 1 246 280 Z\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <text x=\"240\" y=\"220\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"20\" fill=\"#2563eb\" font-weight=\"bold\">Î¸</text>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"180\" x2=\"310\" y2=\"180\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"255\" y=\"195\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\">r</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"340\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">Area = (Î¸/360Â°) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 2: Sector Area</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> A circle has radius 6. What is the area of a 120Â° sector?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²<br>\n  Sector Area = (120/360) Ã— Ï€(6Â²)<br>\n  Sector Area = (1/3) Ã— 36Ï€<br>\n  Sector Area = 12Ï€\n</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 3: Finding the Angle</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> A sector with radius 8 has an area of 16Ï€. What is the central angle?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²<br>\n  16Ï€ = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€(8Â²)<br>\n  16Ï€ = (Î¸/360) Ã— 64Ï€<br>\n  16 = (Î¸/360) Ã— 64<br>\n  16/64 = Î¸/360<br>\n  1/4 = Î¸/360<br>\n  Î¸ = 90Â°\n</p>\n\n\n  <p style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #92400e; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">âš¡ Quick Trick:</p>\n  <p style=\"font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #78350f; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n    For common angles, memorize the fractions:<br>\n    â€¢ 90Â° = 1/4 of circle<br>\n    â€¢ 120Â° = 1/3 of circle<br>\n    â€¢ 180Â° = 1/2 of circle<br>\n    â€¢ 270Â° = 3/4 of circle\n  </p>\n\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Complete Formula Comparison</h3>\n\n<table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem;\">\n  <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\">\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Shape</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Perimeter</strong></strong>/Length</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.85rem;\">Area</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Full Circle</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">C = 2Ï€r</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">A = Ï€rÂ²</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Arc</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">L = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">â€”</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Sector</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">â€”</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">A = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Formulas Summary</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Fraction:</strong> Î¸/360</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Arc Length:</strong> (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Sector Area:</strong> (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Full Circle:</strong> C = 2Ï€r, A = Ï€rÂ²</li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Arc Length = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>The fraction Î¸/360 represents the portion of the circle</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Common angles: 90Â°=1/4, 120Â°=1/3, 180Â°=1/2</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Arc Length = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>The fraction Î¸/360 represents the portion of the circle</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Common angles: 90Â°=1/4, 120Â°=1/3, 180Â°=1/2</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n<div style=\"background: #f0fdf4; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 3rem 0 2rem 0; border-left: 4px solid #10b981;\">\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">âœ“ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Arc Length = (Î¸/360) Ã— 2Ï€r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Sector Area = (Î¸/360) Ã— Ï€rÂ²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>The fraction Î¸/360 represents the portion of the circle</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Common angles: 90Â°=1/4, 120Â°=1/3, 180Â°=1/2</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
